        .case-study__industry-insights
            .anchor#insights
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Industry Insights
                        %h3 Holistic Pet Food & Buyer Behavior
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .industry-insights__section
                            %p.insights-header The holistic pet food market
                            %p The natural and holistic pet food space is growing rapidly, driven by rising demand for minimally processed, human-grade nutrition that aligns with wellness trends. More pet owners now prioritize whole-food ingredients, clean labels, and sustainability, with many owners willing to pay more for premium products.
                            .industry-insights__stats
                                .columns
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b1
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                $57.2B
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                projected global organic and natural pet food market by 2033, up 82% from 2024
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b1
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                55%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of millennial pet owners open to holistic supplements before conventional medication
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b1
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                60%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                more likely for Millenials to purchase organic pet food than other generations
                            .industry-insights__bullets
                                %ul
                                    %li.b1
                                        %span
                                            This is a growing market with growing expectations.
                                        A category projected to nearly double by 2033 means more competition arriving alongside more informed buyers. The brand that earns trust digitally wins.
                                    %li.b1
                                        %span
                                            Millennials are values-driven.
                                        Over half prioritize holistic approaches and are willing to pay more for products that align with their values. They respond to authenticity and proof.
                                    %li.b1
                                        %span
                                            The buyer is already converted. 
                                        The holistic pet food shopper arrives having done the research. Ingredient transparency and sourcing specificity are the conversion levers. The site's job is to confirm they made the right choice.
                        .industry-insights__section
                            %p.insights-header Pet owner digital behavior
                            %p Understanding how pet owners shop, research, and decide shaped the navigation structure, content hierarchy, and the product quiz feature priority.
                            .industry-insights__stats
                                .columns
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b2
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                +113%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                rise in searches for low-calorie pet food. Frozen and fresh options searches are up 111%
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b2
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                61%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of pet parents prioritize ingredient transparency when choosing pet food
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b2
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                59%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of organic and natural pet food purchases in the US are made online, through subscriptions or pet-specific platforms
                            .industry-insights__bullets
                                %ul
                                    %li.b2
                                        %span
                                            Decision fatigue is real in this category. 
                                        With raw, frozen, dehydrated, and fresh options all competing, customers get overwhelmed. A product quiz reduces friction and increases confidence at the moment of purchase.
                                    %li.b2
                                        %span
                                            Ingredient transparency is a baseline expectation.
                                        Nearly two thirds of pet parents are scrutinizing labels before purchasing. Content hierarchy and ingredient visibility are conversion requirements.
                                    %li.b2
                                        %span
                                            The purchase journey is digital.
                                        With nearly 6 in 10 natural pet food purchases happening online, the website is the primary storefront.
        .case-study__competitive-audit
